The paper deals with social choice mechanisms, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). It also involves the use of randomized algorithms (cs.AI) and the analysis of their performance (cs.LG). The concept of sample complexity is related to computational complexity and machine learning (cs.DS). Finally, the paper discusses the properties of different mechanisms and their impact on social welfare, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
